org.ksoap2.transport

Class HttpsServiceConnectionSE

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ksoap2.transport.HttpsServiceConnectionSE
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ServiceConnection
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    HttpsServiceConnectionSEIgnoringConnectionClose

    public class HttpsServiceConnectionSE
extends Object
implements ServiceConnection
    HttpsServiceConnectionSE is a service connection that uses a https url connection and requires explicit setting of host, port and file. The explicit setting is necessary since pure url passing and letting the Java URL class parse the string does not work properly on Android. Links for reference:
    Author:
    Manfred Moser
    See Also:
    "http://stackoverflow.com/questions/2820284/ssl-on-android-strange-issue", "http://stackoverflow.com/questions/2899079/custom-ssl-handling-stopped-working-on-android-2-2-froyo", "http://code.google.com/p/android/issues/detail?id=2690", "http://code.google.com/p/android/issues/detail?id=2764", "https://gist.github.com/908048" There can be problems with the certificate of theof the server on older android versions. You can disable SSL for the versions only e.g. with an approach like this.

      • HttpsServiceConnectionSE

        public HttpsServiceConnectionSE(String host,
                        int port,
                        String file,
                        int timeout)
                         throws IOException
        Create the transport with the supplied parameters.
        Parameters:
        host - the name of the host e.g. webservices.somewhere.com
        port - the http port to connect on
        file - the path to the file on the webserver that represents the webservice e.g. /api/services/myservice.jsp
        timeout - the timeout for the connection in milliseconds
        Throws:
        IOException
